<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 12:48AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Beaver and eastern
Texas Counties through 115 AM CDT...
At 1247 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles east of Hooker, or 16 miles southwest of Liberal, moving east
at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Guymon, Beaver, Hooker, Tyrone, Forgan, Optima, Hardesty, Elmwood,
Adams, Boyd, Floris, Bryans Corner, Baker, Mocane, Turpin and Balko.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
